Bakal's tenant: The stoves are heating up, he signed a higher rent.
An imposing elderly man walked out the door of the Byty RPG company's customer center from the "coal baron" Zdenek Bakal, the largest private owner of apartments for rent in the Czech Republic.
He was carrying under his arm a file with three new leases for three apartments: his own, that of his daughter and his son who is serving a sentence.
Deregulation has increased the rent for these three people.
Instead of paying 3500 the son will have to pay from next year for a 2+1 apartment of second category 4100 crowns.
“And there is no hot water and the heating runs on solid fuel,” points to his son’s new contract the man who has the power to sign.
"But I signed it anyway," he explains, half angry and half resigned.
The citizen association of apartments BytyOKD.cz, which described the new rental conditions as "immoral and indecent", advises tenants not to sign and wait until December 7, when a notice will be published to explain the method to follow to claim.
But man reacts to this with a gesture of the hand.
"One says that, the other says something else" frowning.
The Ostrava region becomes the laboratory of deregulation.
After the New Year, this is what awaits most apartments in the Czech Republic whose rents do not correspond to the market price.
For this reason, Aktualne.cz has decided to personally visit the "laboratory".
The RPG waiting room on Havirovska street is one of the four in the Ostrava region and is already full on Tuesday at 09:00 a.m.
Right next to the door stands a guard from a security company with a device to call customers.
A special button, "rent 2011", is lit on the touch screen.
One press and a paper with a number comes out of the device.
You don't have time to read your number "157" as your number is already starting to light up on the big screen under the waiting room top.
In a fraction of a second, it's your turn.
After a short time, an old couple arrives to inquire about the rent, but the new rents do not seem to concern the people in the waiting room.
The majority of people have come to solve common problems as everywhere - request for repairs, events concerning insurance and others.
In the Ostrava region, people from more than 44,000 apartments in the RPG portfolio have been receiving mail with new leases in their mailboxes since about mid-November.
RPG Byty offers them rent increases of 15 to 38 percent.
The special window for new rents has been open to the public since 18 November.
"It's been running for almost a week, so it's still on trial," answers, after a moment of hesitation, the employee behind the counter when the client introduces himself as a journalist.
The deregulation and former miners’ apartments of Bakal are a very sensitive local subject.
The deputy speaker of the parliament and native of the Ostrava region Lubomir Zaoralek of the Social Democrats reported on this fairly consistently before the elections and it now fills the local newspapers.
“Twenty years after them, I want a new floor.”
"They didn't even change me a put...n of board in the toilets, relieves himself in introduction the man mentioned.
However, they are mostly, according to employees, retirees who come to be sure that they will receive a discount on the new rent price if they sign now as promised RPG in a special offer.
This is a rebate of half the amount of the rent that will be received by other tenants who have signed their new contract before December 15.
But the "deregulation" window on Havirovaska Street is really not overwhelmed by questions.
"Of the 360 customers who came yesterday, only 40 to 50 came for rent," the employee said at the counter.
And yet RPG puts both on its website and in the showcases of individual interviews on rents when necessary.
If the two parties do not agree on the rent, an independent court will make the decision.
"This is not about threats but only about informing about the unique and legitimate way to act legally," RPG said on its website.
"No one is going to go to court here," one of the RPG Byty employees thinks, and the man in the street in front of the customer center agrees with her.
“I have 13,000 kroner to retire and I have 5,000 kroner left to eat, I don’t have enough to go to court,” he says.
The employee suddenly feels uncomfortable.
"We'll see."
"Mr. Zaoralek in the media is asking that no one sign and so people are waiting," she said.
Rent regulation ends in the Czech Republic with the beginning of 2011 and the increases, according to RPG Byty, are an economic necessity.
"And, moreover, the current rents still do not reach the level necessary for the simple maintenance of the fund for housing," recalls Pavel Klimes, director of the residential portfolio of the company RPG Byty, that it is precisely the negligence of the fund for housing that makes the tenant angry is the main reason for the increase in rent.
However in 5 years between 2005 and 2010 RPG was able with rents to invest in apartments 4 billion, in four years from 2011 to 2014 this should make 5.2 billion.
The large screen hanging from the ceiling in front of the upholstered armchairs in the waiting room on Havirosvka Street, however, repeats some information indicated in red.
“The rent increase in 2011 is 15 percent and concerns no less than 31,200 apartments or more than 90 percent of RPG apartments.”
“And it will always be at most 7.50 Czech crowns per m2 per month,” the screen reads.
The 38 percent increase concerns only 400 apartments in the RPG portfolio.
"In these cases, it is an increase of a very low sum of 19.66 Czech crowns per m2," adds RPG.
Next year the rent will remain the same for 2600 apartments.
RPG Byty promises that deregulation will not cause a radical but gradual increase over 4 to 8 years.
It adds other commitments: all the money from the rent increase (see graph) is returned to the apartments in the form of heating savings - new windows and heating.
Those who sign the agreement on the rent increase have priority.
The nursery school is also part of the offices understood by the architects.
the Avriopoint office building in Brno is the new headquarters of the company Arch. Design.
No one could have expected that it also houses a mini kindergarten with everything you need - colorful walls, imaginative furniture, toys and finally a miniature playground on the terrace.
Since October of last year, children of Arch. design employees can go there.
The architectonic project company Arch. Design., whose workshops have produced a large number of constructions in Brno, has imagined its mini enterprise nursery school since the first drafts of the Avriopoint building.
It employs about 90 people, mostly of child-bearing age, and it was important to it that women architects and project managers could quickly return to work.
Along with reduced time work contracts, kindergarten is a bonus offered to its employees by the company Arch. Design. as part of its social program.
Builders and architects thus have the opportunity to combine caring work with care for children.
It was the employees of Arch.Design. themselves who designed this nursery school and with the support of the management they were able to obtain an endowment from the European Union and the Ministry of Labour and Social Affairs.
The mini-kindergarten is financed by the European Social Fund through the Human Resources Operational Programme and the State Budget of the Czech Republic.
Thanks to the funding (up to 2.8 million Czech crowns) they were able to buy equipment and appliances and after two years ensure qualified personnel as well as the start-up.
After the use of the funding endowment (two years) the company Arch. Design. has the obligation after 3 years to operate the mini kindergarten on its own funds.
The preparation of the project took a year and it was the company Economy rating that helped to apply for staffing.
Child care is provided by qualified staff, all day a nurse and kindergarten teacher take care of the children. children can go to kindergarten without age limitation but they are more than three yearsoldfor the most part.
As it is a "mini kindergarten" there can only be 5 children present at the same time, but during the day there are more who replace themselves.
The operation of the school is flexible according to the needs of the parents and the children of all employees have the same right to use this school without regard to the hierarchical position.
Although this is individual care and education, the mini kindergarten curriculum is comparable to that for pre-school education.
The children are not just playing there, but quality teaching is also guaranteed - from the beginning to the preparation for school benches English is taught.
The class is equipped not only with imaginative toys and games but also with a computer that children can use.
The presence of small children in society creates a friendly and positive environment.
Parents can at any time control their child and not have the stress of a delay to pick up the children at a school far from the parents' workplace.
Parents therefore use their working time in the most productive way.
It is not surprising that a natural relationship of loyalty is created between the employee and the employer.
Arch.Design is thus listed among the companies that offer a bonus of choice for the recruitment of new employees and that are friendly to the family and through this program strengthens HR marketing.
The bone house still fascinates after 100 years. Take a look inside Gaudi.
The roof looks like the back of a prehistoric saurian, the staircase looks like a dinosaur spine and the balconies look like open fish mouths.
This is how the Casa Battlo house in Barcelona by the architect Antoni Gaudi is.
Due to its organic forms, the house received from the locals the nickname of Bone House.
Organic shapes, wild colors, unusual use of stones, fragments of tiles and mosaic, facade reminiscent of scales and everywhere present curves, this is all that is epic for Antoni Gaudi's Art Nouveau.
The front facade of the house unfolds its dream lines, its pleasant colors and textures that recall nature and animals.
During a more detailed observation we see the geometry, the rhythm and the order thought with precision.
At night the facade of the house becomes even more dramatic and is lit in such a way that the impression of brightness of the colors is reinforced.
The winding and twisting of the shapes also appears in the interiors with the same measure.
The wood copies in waves the window frames, the balustrades, the decorative elements of the doors, the eyelet and the slats.
The Battlo house, which stands in the Eixample district on the Passeig de Gracia shopping street at number 43, was born from the construction of an 1877 house by the architect Emilio Sala Cortes.
The reconstruction took place over two years and the house was completed in 1906.
The investor, Joseph Battlo, a wealthy entrepreneur, first insisted on demolishing the old building and building a brand new one but quickly accepted Gaudi's idea of an unusual and cheaper reconstruction.
But the idea of Casa Battlo as a multi-unit house was not conceived by Gaudi alone.
The architect Josep Maria Jujol worked with him.
It is precisely on his project that the decorations for an apartment of representation of the owner of the building and the use of the mosaic for the facade were born.
Other artists and creators have also worked on the fa<0xC3><0xA7>ade.
The joint work for the plans of Casa Battlo began with a successful cooperation between Jujol and Gaudi.
Jujol participated in the construction of Gaudi's Casa Mila and the Park Guell in which there are other works of Gaudi.
The locals nicknamed the house hot just after it was finished because of its organic shapes "the Bone House".
Others, in view of the specific mechanism of opening the windows have called it "the house that yawns".
It is said that at the top of the building there is a sword similar to that of St. George the patron saint of Catalonia.
Other sculptural elements of the building contain hidden religious motifs.
Gaudi thought for the house a unique system in its time of central heating,with ventilation vents and typical fireplaces.
Their inclination of 45 degrees seems strange.
During the creation Gaudi absolutely did not comply with the construction guidelines of the time and did not let himself be hindered by them.
At the beginning of the construction he obtained from the city the permit to build, knowing, of course, that the data on the reconstruction plans were so vague that two years later during the finishing the city council was horrified and asked for modifications.
For example, members of the city council did not like the building pillars impinging on the public sidewalk.
There was never any modification, but, on the contrary, only 15 days after the call of the city Josep Battlo asked (and obtained satisfaction) the authorization to rent the two highest floors.
The owner moved to the lower floors.
In the gallery on the second floor there was a common living room and on the third a bedroom and a private part of the apartment.
The ground floor was rented to a jewelry store.
The entire six-storey house is shared by a staircase that leads to an independent roof terrace.
All right angles and straight lines were cancelled by the basic elements of the reconstruction and replaced by curved walls.
Gaud<0xC3><0xAD> also worked on the modern concept of linking spaces.
The common part can be completely connected by opening the doors of the living rooms and the high society can communicate comfortably or limit themselves to the private space for more intimate interviews.
The house with the reconstruction of Gaudi received besides new facades a non-traditional roofing and two floors more.
Gaudi’s play with light is also impressive, blue and white glazed tiles with which the inner courtyard is decorated and with the skylights.
The two-color play gives maximum light in all floors of the house.
It was enough simply to bet on the principle that white reflects more than the dark which on the contrary absorbs the rays of the sun.
The Casa Battlo which was inscribed in 2005 in the Unesco World Heritage Fund can be visited by everyone.
On the first floor of the house is the most spacious and splendid apartment accessible to the public.
The owners decided to take this step in 2002 on the occasion of the 150th anniversary of the birth of the famous designer.
They continued the visits as they found it to be a lucrative venture and they expanded the scope of the visits to the common areas and attic including the roof terraces.
The entrance ticket to the monument is really cheap and costs 16.50 euros; students, pensioners, groups and holders of tourist cards have 20 percent discount.
The sum is still above the price of entry to Gaudi's other buildings in the city.
If you want to feel the real atmosphere of the house with its fantastic turrets, you must quickly find a comrade among the inhabitants of the building and visit the house completely.
How to choose a mattress and a box spring: women have other criteria than men.
No ostentatious frame, but rather the quality of the surface reserved for sleeping, so the mattress and the box spring give a real basis for a good bed.
They must of course complement each other harmoniously to please a concrete user.
During the choice several things are decisive,: weight, height, age, state of health as well as the sex of the owner.
The type of interior in which we are going to place the mattress and the box spring is also important.
A typical example?
For example in the country house where one does not sleep continuously latex mattresses are not appropriate because they "warm up" gently.
In addition, they have a higher weight than standard polyurethane mattresses.
It is necessary to return them frequently.
If they do not also have enough ventilation ducts in the heart and if they also remain on a solid board, they retain moisture. Mold can also form there.
Habit is also decisive in the choice.
Anyone who spends time abroad, where very thick mattresses with a softening layer are frequently used, will hardly feel good on a low, hard surface.
“That’s how all the hockey players who come back from the NHL complain that they can’t sleep there.”
“For their tired shoulders, feet and ribs, they needed mattresses with a softening layer of lazy foam.”
“Such mattresses are also recommended for people who suffer from diabetes who have a disorder of the nervous system that therefore misassume “information” of the joints and skin,” explains Sylva Adamczikova, who specializes in upholstered furniture.
That's why a few years ago the mattress with lazy foam conquered hockey players as well as other customers.
"Today everything is going well, Tempur, the Italian Magnifex but also the Czech Tropico have for example suitable mattresses.
You don’t have to be an NHL guy to enjoy a lazy lather.
This “miracle” simply works.
It optimizes its rigidity and shape according to the absorbed heat or adapts to the heat of your body.
Nothing puts pressure on you and you won’t turn around in the night like after a tough game.
You just sleep better.
Lazy foam also works as a protection against squares.
For the choice of mattress according to your size, add the length of the feet, about 21/34 cm.
A man and a woman of a size of 180cm therefore need a bed of 210/220 cm.
The minimum width for each for a double bed should be 90 cm or a total of 180 cm.
For single beds, for example, it is recommended to take at least 120 / 140 cm.
It is convenient in case of visit.
'However, there is a simple rule for the width of the bed: when lying on your back you should lay your hands comfortably with the elbows slightly bent. Helena Prokopova, President of the Association of Quilting and Decorators who has been dedicated for several years to the problem of healthy sleep and ergonomics of furniture and teaches it in specialized schools.
For a double bed everyone needs their own mattress and mattress, so be careful however during the purchase to choose the height of the mattress.
Otherwise you will only have to mount the box spring at different heights and this is not feasible on all bed frames.
Foam mattresses should have a minimum height of 14 cm, spring mattresses at least 15 cm, so count for the shape and ventilation layer at least three centimeters.
"To the touch or sitting on the mattress you should not feel the springs," warns Helena Prokopova.
Each mattress requires a specific type of box spring.
The bed-sunk bed, when the mattress and the bed-sunk bed are united like Siamese sisters, has nothing to do in the bedrooms.
The mattresses hurt very badly; it should not be washed, which is commonly done today.
And since during the night we normally sweat from 0.2 to 0.75 l of sweat it is clear that after 5/7 years, the mattress begins to resemble a large (and clogged) sieve.
For this reason, specialists refuse to advertise for a life of 25 years for a mattress or a lifetime warranty.
But all to his but.
And for this an experience advice from the sellers: for a mattress of 120/140cm, give up, for the coating of the mattress, hygiene or washing but instead add a protective mattress that you can easily remove and wash.
And even if nowadays it is common to manufacture coatings with zipper for the whole set, that is to say that after opening one has two parts (for washing and the size of the washing machine it is very important!) otherwise the manipulation for large models (and for a single person) becomes when they are removed a fight between a light weight and a heavy weight on a ring.
Do you have a rigid board in your bed instead of a box spring?
No way!
Maximum for a bed intended for visitors for one night only.
However, equip the board (if there are no) with ventilation holes and use the spring mattress with a minimum height of 15cm with bag springs (from Germany Taschenfederken) and a ventilation layer.
A polyurethane mattress should not be part of a bed of this type.
For single-position slatted beds with 14/18 slats, latex mattresses or so-called sandwiches (perhaps the combination of latex and coconut), are the ideal but it will always be better for you to have a mattress with more slats, 28 and above, where the slats are lined up in the lower part of the possible kidneys and thus stiffen.
For mattresses with several positions it is not necessary to take a spring mattress because it does not respond to changes in position.
Next to the adjustment of the rigidity of the slats, it is also possible to install what is called a shoulder cradle.
This is a special connection of the slats that makes it possible to press or even tilt the slat so that the shoulder of the sleeper "fits in" well.
For men who have "shoulders as wide as their backs", this is really an important thing.
This thing is already considered by mattress manufacturers who for "males" have begun to use a softening area at the level of the shoulders.
But they also think about women - they again offer them a softer surface at the hips.
For the most difficult customer there are winged or platelet bed bases with what is called a multi-force suspension.
The pressure spreads to more points and diinuates the tension.
But of course, be careful, as soon as you use a bad pillow (large and inflated with air) on good mattresses and box spring, the "plus" disappears.
The basic rule is a simple pillow: the pillow must support the head and its tips must reach only the shoulders, so that the shoulder muscles can rest.
The recommended size is 50X60 cm which Scandinavians prefer per exmple.
When lying on the side, the pillow should level the height of the shoulders (with the shoulder cradle of the box spring or the softened area in the mattress).
Modern mattresses still have something in common with the first ones based on straw and herbs.
Manufacturers still use natural materials or mixtures.
The trend is also towards organic mattresses.
Petroleum-based raw materials, from which polyurethane is made, are replaced by natural oils, such as soybean oil.
Almost all known manufacturers use soy.
“The term ‘organic’ for mattresses means that the heart is made from natural products,” says Petr Vasicek of Tropico Plus.
Natural materials are also used for mattress coverings; one of the first was aloe vera.
But you can add micro-capsules that develop fragrances of the forest or lavender.
There are differences between men and women.
While the extract of birch plants so that the mattress coating absorbs heat and cools the body, "cools" the man, the coatings "warm" women.
The red pepper extract accelerates blood circulation and is therefore warmer for the weaker sex.
The current favorites?
Mattresses made from cold foam (it has more pores with a disturbed cellular structure so more breathable than standard polyurethane and has more elasticity.
The combination of different stiffnesses of cold foams gives polyzone mattresses that know precisely where the head, lower back and feet are.
You will pay a quality mattress from 7000 crowns and more.
Those that are characterized by their health parameters have less VAT and are taken as instruments for health.
In the Czech Republic, Gumotex took first place.
Saving for the mattress and the box spring is not easy.
From time to time we can have as part of special actions on the part of manufacturers or producers two mattresses for the price of one.
For example, Magniflex offers Duofreeze mattresses with Memory memory foam sewn to the coating for 11990 crowns.
Of course, you can take the second one for free.
The era of lazy or viscoelastic foams with an open cellular structure and great thickness was started with the Tempur material at a "cosmic" pace.
It started as a material for NASA because astronauts were suffering from the start-up of huge load factors.
The Tempur softens in the heat and hardens, on the contrary, in the cold.
It therefore adapts perfectly to the warm human body and distributes optimal pressure to it.
It is therefore ideal against bad sleep and for an increase in comfort during sleep.
Viscoelastic foams are used not only for mattresses but also for health products, such as special foot cushions that relieve the legs and venous system.
For example, Czech manufacturers use EucathermC or Twinsaver foam or the same type.
Devices to track people are increasingly in demand by parents who want to monitor their children.
The fear for their child leads more and more people to think about monitoring them through a GPS.
The system, set up at the beginning to search for cars, can also be used to track the movement of people and help in some cases, such as that of little Anicka Janatkova.
The instrument is currently as big as a matchbox but will soon be the size of a watch.
The case of little Anicka moved a large number of people and they began to look for ways to better protect their children.
Even if the price is to disturb their privacy.
“We are trying to tell everyone that this is not espionage but just another way to decrease the likelihood of another tragedy,” says Petr Pilin of MAcro Weil, one of the providers of tracking devices in the Czech market.
"I admit that there may be cases of misuse of such devices, such as putting it in the bag of a person who is not aware, but I have not yet encountered such cases."
“The majority of people are customers who actually buy the product for safety reasons,” Pilin adds.
According to him, children should always know for what purposes "the box" is used and how to use it in an emergency.
Child psychologist Dana Bockova points out that if the child does not want to wear something like this on him, he will get rid of it.
“And even the smallest ones can show great creativity when it comes to purposely getting rid of something when they don’t want to be under control.”
“Mobile phones, which can cut themselves like these tracing devices, have already led parents to long waits,” Bockova says.
According to her, the fact that this type of device can help in case of aggression is very questionable.
"If it is a prepared abduction, the perpetrator will do everything to ensure that the child does not have an electronic device that can locate him."
“Right now, it’s the phone.”
"As soon as the tracking devices are developed, they (criminals) will also look for them because the sale will be supported by an advertising campaign."
“In such cases the criminals will always be ahead of the police,” says the psychologist.
She admits, however, that such devices can help during an unprepared assault by a pedophile.
According to Robert Cech of RC Monitoring, which offers tracking services for both cars and people, having this type of device can help, even if it is destroyed in the event of an assault.
"The device can be set to be in regular transmission after a specified period of time."
"In the event that the device is destroyed, it remains the last position of the person concerned."
“The more expensive devices also have an inclinometer that immediately signals the position of the person who has slid and is lying down without moving,” says Cech.
According to him, so-called smart mobile phones that are equipped with a navigation system can offer a comparable service after having formatted it with a special software.
The problem with current tracking systems is that it is either a device similar to those worn as a pendant the size of a matchbox or smaller telephone devices.
We can always lose them.
According to Pilina of the company Macro Weil, this is why tests are currently being conducted to make devices that look like common digital watches.
"This will have the advantage that the potential aggressor will not be able to recognize the tracking device."
“Or he’ll realize it after a while, which will have given the police a little bit more time,” he adds.
Whether the tracing device is developed in the form of a bracelet or pendant, it will always use the same technology as when tracing cars.
It is a combination of position acquisition systems using GPS (which is commonly used in auto-navigation) and a mobile phone function that alerts a vehicle's current position.
