Americans have a new “smart weapon”
The U.S. military has sent a new “smart” weapon, known only as the XM-25, to Afghanistan.
The generals believe that this new automatic rifle will have an influence on the conflict there with the Taliban and “will change the game” for their benefit.
The new weapon is like a super accurate cannon
Its projectiles are guided by laser with an accuracy of a few meters.
The special 25 mm ammunition developed for this rifle and containing a highly explosive, works in fact like small grenades.
The munitions can be programmed in such a way that they will explode in contact with the target but also at any point in their ballistic trajectory.
It can therefore be used against an enemy who hides behind an obstacle, a wall or a ditch.
He is also not protected from above and when a deadly rain of steel splinters falls on him, it can put him out of action as well.
According to Richard Audette who took part in the development of the XM-25, the new rifle is the first infantry weapon that uses “smart” technology.
The soldier essentially uses it in such a way that he finds the target, sends him a laser beam that determines the distance, thus obtaining a precise point of sight, according to which he corrects his site sight and presses on the trigger.
"Let's say you aimed at 543 meters."
“When you press the trigger, the weapon charges and fires at the distance of 543 meters plus or minus 1, 2, 3 meters,” Audette said.
