The University of the Ice
At the "Gelato University" in Bologna, ice confectioners are prepared for the best seasons of the year.
The three-day initiation course for future glaciers was very successful and attracted visitors from all over the world.
By the way, where did all the ice come from?
The glacier and the ice machine.
The glacier, that is to say in German the somewhat old-fashioned ice confectioner, manufactures the cream according to all the rules of the Italian art of ice-making.
The ice turbine removes the ice cream from the refrigerated display case with a spatula, places it in the waffle, and then starts selling it.
To find out, one does not need to go to Anzola dell'Emilia in the province of Bologna.
